# Obsolete string, do not remove;Using three distinct interactive graphic representations — Graph, Clock and List — Lightbeam enables you to examine individual third parties over time and space, identify where they connect to your online activity and provides ways for you to engage with this unique view of the Web.
Tajin nokisäx oxi' jalajöj taq tz'etoj silon taq wachib'äl — wachib'äl, q'ijub'äl chuqa' cholb'äl — Lightbeam nuya' q'ij chawe najäch pa (oxi' | ka'i') peraj richin nanik'oj chi kijujunal pa ruwi' ramaj chuqa' k'ojlib'äl, naya' retal akuchi' nikixïm ki' rik'in ri asamaj pa k'amab'ey chuqa' nusüj k'ïy taq rub'eyal richin yato'on rik'in re ruyonil tz'etoj re' richin ri Ajk'amaya'l.


;The default Graph view provides a real time visualization of every site you visit and all third party requests made from your browser.
Ri rutz'etoj wachib'äl kan ruk'amon wi pe nuq'alajisxaj jun tz'etoj pa ri ramaj kichin chi kijujunal ri ruxaq k'amaya'l ri xke'atz'ët chuqa' ronojel ri taq kik'utuj aj rox kib'anon chi re ri awokik'amaya'l.


;The Graph view also provides adjustable filters that allow you to visualize more types of data at a glance.
Ri wachib'äl tz'etoj chuqa' e k'o nuk'uj taq chayub'äl, ri nuya' q'ij richin ye'atz'ët ch'aqa' chik ruwäch taq tzij rik'in jun tz'etoj.


;The List view provides more options for drilling down into individual sites.
Ri cholb'äl tz'etoj nuya' ch'aqa' chik taq cha'oj richin yakanon chi kipam ri taq ichinan ruxaq k'amaya'l.


;Site preferences in the List view enable you to block sites from connecting to your Firefox browser, watch sites you’re interested in or hide sites you don’t want to see visualized.
Ri taq rajowaxik ruxaq k'amaya'l pa ri cholb'äl tz'etoj, nuya' q'ij chawe ye'aq'ät ri taq ruxaq k'amaya'l, ri nikixïm ki' rik'in ri Firefox awokik'amaya'l, ye'atz'ët taq ruxaq k'amaya'l ri nawajo' ye'atz'ët o chuqa' ye'awewaj taq ruxaq k'amaya'l ri man nawajo' ta chi yeq'alajin pe.


;Lightbeam also offers an information panel that provides additional details about the site you selected and the sites it has connected to.
Lightbeam chuqa' nuya' chawe jun rupas etamab'äl, ri nuq'alajisaj taq rutz'aqat kib'anikil chi rij ri ruxaq k'amaya'l xacha' chuqa' ri taq ruxaq k'amaya'l e'atz'eton.


;The origins of Lightbeam
Ri taq rukutamil Lightbeam


;Lightbeam began in July 2011 as Collusion, a personal project by Mozilla software developer <a href="%s">Atul Varma</a>.
Lightbeam xutikirisaj pa ruwuq rik' ri juna' 2011 achi'el Collusion, jun nuk'samaj pa ruwi' b'anöy rukema' Mozilla<a href="%s">Atul Varma</a>.


;Inspired by the book, <em>The Filter Bubble</em>, Atul created an experimental add-on to visualize browsing behavior and data collection on the Web.
Tzeqeliben ruma ri wuj, <em>The Filter Bubble</em>,Atul xunük' jun soltojtob'enel chi tz'aqat richin nik'ut ri rub'eyal nub'än richin nikanon chuqa' yerumöl ri taq tzij pa Ajk'amaya'l


;In February 2012, Gary Kovacs, Mozilla CEO at the time, introduced the Collusion add-on in a <a href="%s">TED talk</a> (now one of the most watched TED talks of all time) about exposing online tracking.
Pa ruka'n rik'in ri juna' 2012, Gary Kovacs, pa ri q'ijul ri' CEO richin Mozilla, xuk'üt ri tz'aqat Collusion pa jun<a href="%s">TED tzijonem</a> (wakami jun chi ke ri TED tzijonem yalan nitz'et), akuchi' nuq'alajisaj pa ruwi' ri kanoxïk pa k'amab'ey.


;In September 2012, Mozilla joined forces with faculty and student researchers at <a href="%s">Emily Carr University of Art + Design</a> to develop and implement visualizations for the add-on.
Pa rub'elej rik' ri juna' 2012, Mozilla xutün ruchuq'a' kik'in rutijoxela' <a href="%s">Emily Carr richin Na'ojil + Wachib'enïk</a> richin nikinük' chuqa' niya' kisamajib'al taq tz'etoj chi re ri tz'aqat.


;With the support of the Ford Foundation and the Natural Sciences and Engineering Research Council (NSERC), Collusion has been re-imagined as Lightbeam and was launched in the fall of 2013.
Rik'in ruto'ik ri Ford Moloj chuqa' ri Natural Sciences and Engineering Research Council (NSERC), Collusion xnuk' chik achi'el Lightbeam chuqa' xelesäx pa rutz'apijäb' ri juna' 2013.


